Comment: The gold standard of opening moves.
The Center Counter Defense, a very sharp line.
The immediate recapture usually leads to immediate tactics.
The usual, and good, response. Now White cannot advance the QP without causing a self-pin.
Benschop develops aggressively. She is trying to exploit White's advantage in time this line generates.
Gruenenwald proceeds with her own development.
Submitting to the self-pin in order to protect one Bishop and open a line for the other.
Gruenenwald has neutralized the advantage in time with this move.
Breaking the pin and threatening a counter. White's Knight can now move with a discovery to Black's Queen.
Clearing a diagonal for the Queen's potential retreat.
Clearing the way to castle Q-side, with a pin on the Black KP.
Benschop exploits the discovery on the Queen, with a further threat of N-B7 ch winning the Exchange. Gruenenwald resigns.
